document_data.name: Shan Nala
document_data.mainbody: '''Shan Nala''' was the highest peak of the [[Raurin Alta]] mountains of the [[Raurin]] desert.
document_data.Geography: Shan Nala stood on the far eastern end of the mountain range near [[Howling Gap]] and [[Solon]]. It overlooked the peaks of [[Leopard Shan]] and [[Jorhat Shan]] on the plains below.
document_data.Description: At an elevation of {{SI|13951|ft}}, Shan Nala towered above the other peaks of the Raurin Alta.
